PRINT NODES IN SORTED ORDER

You are given a Binary Search Tree (BST). Your task is to print all the nodes of the BST in sorted order.

INPUT FORMAT

The first line contains an integer N
N is the number of nodes in the BST

The next (N - 1) lines describe the edges of the tree
Each line contains three values:
pi ci Ri

where
pi is the parent node value
ci is the child node value
Ri represents the relationship
L means ci is the left child of pi
R means ci is the right child of pi

OUTPUT FORMAT

Print N space-separated integers representing the node values in sorted order

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ N ≤ 10000
1 ≤ pi, ci ≤ 100000
Ri is either L or R
All node values are distinct

SAMPLE INPUT

7
4 2 L
4 6 R
2 3 R
2 1 L
6 5 L
6 7 R

SAMPLE OUTPUT

1 2 3 4 5 6 7

EXPLANATION

In a Binary Search Tree, inorder traversal gives nodes in sorted order.
So the output is 1 2 3 4 5 6 7.

class Solution {
    public static void printNodes(Node root) {
       if(root==null) 
         return;
       printNodes(root.left);
       System.out.print(root.val+" ");
       printNodes(root.right);
    }
}


